Bauchi State Governor Mohammed Abubakar yesterday presented a budget estimate of N196.722 billion to the House of Assembly for the 2019 fiscal year. Tagged “Budget of Continuity”, it had a recurrent expenditure of N79,196,977,119 and a capital expenditure of N117, 525,434,317. Giving a breakdown of the budget, the Commissioner for State Planning Commission, Magaji Abubakar, said N41,472,337,266 was allocated to the education sector; and N31,326,287,433, to the health sector. Speaker Kawuwa Shehu Damina promised that, the house would do justice to the fiscal document.  Benue dep. gov presents 2019 budget 2018: Borno presents N170b budget Okowa presents N367.09b fiscal proposals for 2019